    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In order to do that, you need to implement a stateMapping that will hold the knowledge of the translation of the index names. Something like:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst search = instantsearch({\r\n  // credentials\r\n  routing: {\r\n    stateMapping: {\r\n      stateToRoute:  function(uiState) {\r\n        return { idx: uiState.sortBy && uiState.sortBy.replace('_production', '') }\r\n      },\r\n      routeToState: function(routeState) {\r\n        return { sortBy: routeState.idx && routeState.idx + '_production' }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe code might need some real testing but that's the general idea.",
    "created_at": "2018-04-19T09:28:30Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2832#issuecomment-382671122",
